data.text: @covid19nz Waste of time getting vacc isn't it.

@covid19nz Look at NZ hospital chart - rate per 100k being hospitalised with Covid in the last week almost same for double vax vs unvax. 75.6% of all covid cases in hospital are vaxxed! https://t.co/MbwGtnVnsn
Book your booster online at https://t.co/n1MblkJep9 or find a walk-in location here: https://t.co/UrErPrNqw1
Find out what happens if you are a Household Contact here: https://t.co/L47MFQFUar
Find out what happens if you test positive here: https://t.co/gwSM4ZsC9F
Find a testing location here: https://t.co/9NKLRiPu34
More information on cases, testing, and vaccine doses can be found in today’s Ministry of Health update: https://t.co/Nx0kdLfWuR

There were also 802 child (paediatric) vaccine doses, which were administered to 5 to 11 year olds throughout New Zealand yesterday. 
  
More than 10.48 million doses have been administered to date.
Yesterday, 6,129 vaccine doses were administered to those aged 12 and over. This includes 5,697 booster doses. This means 72% of those eligible and due for their booster have now received it.
